Color of holotype in preservative (
Fig. 2
): head and body yellowish white; ventral half of pectoral-fin base, abdomen, and ventral half of caudal peduncle with many dark brown dots.

Color of paratype in life ( BPBM 35724 :
Fig. 3
): dorsal half of body and nape transparent with seven broad pink bars containing black blotches, the first on nape extending ventrally to operculum, second under predorsal region, third under rear of first dorsal fin, fourth under anterior half of second dorsal fin, fifth under posterior half of second dorsal fin, sixth on anterior half of caudal peduncle, and seventh on posterior half of caudal peduncle; a pink and black blotch in occipital region; lower half of body deep pink, suffused with a little yellow and densely blotched and dotted with black; lower half of head pink with scattered small black spots; upper half of iris bright red with some yellow dots and a yellow margin on dorsal half of pupil; a white line along dorsal part of vertebral column interrupted by pink and black bars to form a series of eight dashes; all fins translucent pink.
